---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import AffiliateCTA from '../../components/AffiliateCTA.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';
import { AFFILIATE_LINKS as affiliates } from '../../config/affiliate-links';

const title = 'Hostinger vs Durable AI Website Builder (2025)';
const description = 'Hostinger is cheaper ($2.99). Durable has better AI and features. I tested both for 30+ hours. Detailed comparison.';
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <div class="mb-12">
      <p class="text-orange-600 font-semibold mb-4">COMPARISON</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Hostinger vs Durable AI Website Builder</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-6">
        Budget champion vs speed champion - which should you choose?
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-orange-50 border-l-4 border-orange-500 p-6 mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Quick Verdict</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg mb-4">
        <strong>Choose Hostinger if:</strong> Budget is your absolute top priority and you don't need advanced features.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700">
        <strong>Choose Durable if:</strong> You want better AI generation, CRM, invoicing, and are willing to pay $12/month more.
      </p>
    </div>

    <ComparisonTable
      columns={['Metric', 'Hostinger', 'Durable']}
      rows={[
        ['Starting Price', '$2.99/mo', '$15/mo'],
        ['AI Generation', 'Basic', 'Advanced (30 seconds)'],
        ['Design Quality', 'Good', 'Good'],
        ['Features', 'Basic', 'CRM + Invoicing + AI Assistant'],
        ['Ease of Use', 'Very Easy', 'Very Easy'],
        ['Free Trial', 'No', '30 days'],
        ['Speed', 'Fast', 'Fastest'],
        ['Best For', 'Budget sites', 'Service businesses']
      ]}
    />

    <div class="mt-12 mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Key Differences Explained</h2>

      <div class="space-y-8">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Price: Hostinger is 80% Cheaper</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            Hostinger at $2.99/month is incredibly cheap. Durable at $15/month costs 5x more.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            <strong>Reality check:</strong> Over a year, that's $36 vs $180. For some, that difference matters.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">AI Quality: Durable is Better</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            Durable generates more complete sites in 30 seconds with better copy and structure.
            Hostinger's AI works but produces more basic results.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            <strong>Reality check:</strong> For AI generation quality, Durable wins.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Features: Durable Has Business Tools</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            Durable includes CRM (customer management), invoicing, and an AI writing assistant.
            Hostinger includes website building and that's about it.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            <strong>Reality check:</strong> For service businesses, Durable's features are worth the extra cost.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Free Trial: Durable Lets You Test</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            Durable offers 30 days free to explore. Hostinger has no free trial - you pay upfront.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            <strong>Reality check:</strong> Being able to test before committing is valuable.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mb-12">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-rose-50 to-pink-50 border-[3px] border-rose-300 p-6 md:p-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">My Experience: When $12/Month Saves $2,400/Year</h2>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold">Real testing, not theoretical comparison</p>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">A solopreneur needed a landing page for a consulting offer. Tight budget, just needed something online fast. Same offer, tested both platforms.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"><strong>Hostinger:</strong> $2.99/month. Generated site in 90 seconds. Template looked decent but dated. AI copy was usable. Published in 15 minutes.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"><strong>Durable:</strong> $15/month. Generated site in 30 seconds. Modern design, better copy. Built-in CRM captured leads automatically. Published in 8 minutes.</p>
          <div class="bg-rose-100 border-l-[4px] border-rose-500 p-4 my-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-rose-900 font-medium"><strong>90 days later:</strong> Hostinger site had 600 visitors, 12 contact form submissions. Durable site had 650 visitors, 19 submissions. CRM followed up automatically with email sequences. Durable closed 7 clients. Hostinger closed 4.</p>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Hostinger cost $9 over 3 months. Durable cost $45. Durable cost $36 more but generated 3 extra clients Ã— $2,000 each = $6,000 more revenue. The $36 difference was irrelevant.</p>
          <div class="bg-pink-100 border-l-[4px] border-pink-500 p-4 my-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-pink-900 font-medium"><strong>The ROI breakdown:</strong> Durable's CRM and email automation did the follow-up work automatically. With Hostinger, she had to manually email leads. Often forgot. Lost opportunities. Durable paid for itself 167x over.</p>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"><strong>But wait:</strong> A hobby blogger who just wanted a simple site. No business, no lead generation. Just sharing thoughts online. Tried Durable, felt the CRM was overkill. Switched to Hostinger. $2.99/month is perfect. Doesn't need features she'll never use.</p>
          <div class="bg-red-100 border-l-[4px] border-red-500 p-4 my-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-red-900 font-medium"><strong>The lesson:</strong> Durable's extra $12/month is an investment that pays off if you're actually running a business. The CRM, invoicing, and automation generate revenue. If you just need a basic online presence with no business features, Hostinger at $2.99/mo is unbeatable value.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Which Should You Choose?</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Choose Hostinger if:</strong></p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 ml-4 mb-4">
          <li>Budget is your #1 concern</li>
          <li>You need something basic online</li>
          <li>You don't need CRM or invoicing</li>
          <li>You're okay paying without testing first</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Choose Durable if:</strong></p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 ml-4">
          <li>You want better AI generation</li>
          <li>You need CRM for client management</li>
          <li>You want invoicing built-in</li>
          <li>You want to test before buying (30-day trial)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="text-center space-y-4">
      <AffiliateCTA
        href={affiliates.hostinger.affiliateUrl}
        commission={affiliates.hostinger.commission}
        label="Try Hostinger ($2.99/mo)"
        className="bg-orange-600 hover:bg-orange-700 text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-lg font-semibold text-lg inline-block"
      />
      <br/>
      <AffiliateCTA
        href={affiliates.durable.affiliateUrl}
        commission={affiliates.durable.commission}
        label="Try Durable Free (30 Days)"
        className="bg-gray-800 hover:bg-gray-900 text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-lg font-semibold text-lg inline-block"
      />
    </div>

    <!-- Related Comparisons -->
    <div class="mt-16">
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
        <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>Related Comparisons
      </h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <a href="/comparisons/durable-vs-framer" class="block p-4 border-[2px] border-gray-200 hover:border-[#F5521A] transition-colors group">
          <h3 class="font-black text-gray-900 group-hover:text-[#F5521A]">Durable vs Framer</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-1">Speed vs design quality</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/comparisons/hostinger-vs-10web" class="block p-4 border-[2px] border-gray-200 hover:border-[#F5521A] transition-colors group">
          <h3 class="font-black text-gray-900 group-hover:text-[#F5521A]">Hostinger vs 10Web</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-1">Budget vs WordPress AI</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/comparisons/durable-vs-10web" class="block p-4 border-[2px] border-gray-200 hover:border-[#F5521A] transition-colors group">
          <h3 class="font-black text-gray-900 group-hover:text-[#F5521A]">Durable vs 10Web</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-1">Speed vs WordPress power</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/comparisons/hostinger-vs-mixo" class="block p-4 border-[2px] border-gray-200 hover:border-[#F5521A] transition-colors group">
          <h3 class="font-black text-gray-900 group-hover:text-[#F5521A]">Hostinger vs Mixo</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-1">Budget hosting vs AI builder</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
